description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a band 5 staff nurse looking for a challenge in a new exciting role within our Minor Injuries Unit at Frome, Shepton Mallet and West Mendip?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No two days are the same! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves initial assessment , wound care, assessment, and closure , plastering, administrating medication under PGD, and assisting the Nurse Practitioners in their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a dynamic team with a broad scope of advanced practice including both injury and illness, we embrace variety and the challenge of learning something new every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a supportive senior nursing and management team who actively encourage innovation and education in order to achieve the highest standards of care and have a comprehensive CPD programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of your interview, you will be required to show the following: Proof of any essential qualifications stated on the Job Description, proof of NHS payslip if coming from another NHS Organisation and all ID to prove your identity and Right to Work (More details will follow for successful applicants invited to interview)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note&lt;/strong&gt; – the advertised posts are based at Glastonbury AND Frome therefore you must be able to drive . If you seek any clarification please contact us on 01458 836471.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
